The paper deals with permutation groups and their representation using connected graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of context-free grammars and formal languages suggests a connection to computational complexity (cs.CC) and theoretical computer science (cs.THE). Finally, the mention of extension complexity and polytopes indicates a possible connection to linear programming and optimization (cs.LG) and control theory (cs.SY).
